io.proximax.dfms.model.contract

Class Contract

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.proximax.dfms.model.contract.Contract

  • public class Contract
extends java.lang.Object
    Representation of drive contract. Contract is an agreement between client and replicator peers on some amount of disk Space

      • Contract

        public Contract(Cid id,
                io.proximax.core.crypto.PublicKey owner,
                java.util.List<io.proximax.core.crypto.PublicKey> replicators,
                java.math.BigInteger duration,
                java.math.BigInteger created,
                Cid root,
                java.math.BigInteger space)
        Parameters:
        id - CID identifier of Contract's Drive
        owner - owner of the Contract. Has write access on the Contract's Drive and can control it's state.
        replicators - nodes which are responsible for replication of DriveFS
        duration - duration for which the contract is valid TODO blocks or millis
        created - block height when the Contract was started.
        root - CID of Drive's top-level directory. It is used as an entry point to access DriveFS
        space - total physical Space used by Drive on replicator nodes.
